Note: To build from source, you must have the <a href="http://libsdl.org">SDL</a> development library installed.
<br>
<br>

Control notes:
<ul>
<li>Press any button (or key) to start the game.
<li>Use left analog stick (or arrow keys) to move character (up, down, left, right).
<li>F (on keyboard) to toggle fullscreen mode.
<li>B (on keyboard) to adjust screen blow-up factor.
<li>Q or ESC (on keyboard) to quit.
</ul>

Display notes:
<ul>
<li>Default full-screen resolution is 640x480.
<li>Some monitors (like LCD?) don't do well at low resolutions (blurry pixels).
<li>Edit the files in the <i>settings</i> folder to change the full screen resolution (try 1024 for <i>screenWidth.ini</i> and 768 for <i>screenHeight.ini</i>).
<li>Put a zero in <i>fullscreen.ini</i> to make the game start in windowed mode.
</ul>

Credits:
<ul>
<li>All code, music, graphics, fonts, and animation by me.
<li>I used <a href="http://mtpaint.sf.net">mtPaint</a> to make all of the pixel art.
<li>I used the <a href="http://libsdl.org">SDL Library</a> for cross-platform screen, sound, and user input.
<li>I used <a href="http://www.mingw.org">MinGW</a> to build the game for Windows.
</ul>


